# NatureSip: Manufacturing & Production Process

This document outlines the end-to-end process for converting fresh fruits and vegetables into premium powders and tablets.

## 1. Sourcing & Raw Material Intake
- **Origin:** Direct-from-farm procurement in Uttar Pradesh.
- **Criteria:** Pesticide-free, peak ripeness, and high nutrient density.
- **Measurement:** Incoming batches are measured by weight (kg) and Brix level (for fruits) to ensure sugar content consistency.

## 2. Pre-Processing
- **Cleaning:** Multi-stage ultrasonic washing to remove surface contaminants.
- **Peeling/Seeding:** Automated removal of non-edible parts (e.g., mango skins, jamun seeds).
- **Slicing:** Standardized thickness (2-3mm) for uniform drying.

## 3. Flash Drying Technology (Core Process)
NatureSip utilizes high-speed vacuum flash drying to preserve 95% of natural enzymes and vitamins.
- **Temperature:** Low-temperature range (40°C - 55°C) to prevent thermal degradation.
- **Duration:** 15-30 seconds (Flash cycle).
- **Result:** Moisture content reduced to <3%.

## 4. Fine Milling & Sweetening
- **Milling:** Micronization into ultra-fine powder (approx. 50-100 microns).
- **Sweetening:** Manual/Automated mixing with **Dry Honey Powder**. 
  - *Ratio:* 95% Fruit Powder : 5% Dry Honey Powder (Adjustable per fruit type).
- **Agglomeration:** (Optional) Process for improved solubility.

## 5. Compression (Tablets)
For the tablet line (e.g., Amla, Jamun):
- **Pressure:** 10-15 kN compression force.
- **Binder:** Zero artificial binders; Uses natural fruit fiber as a structural matrix.

## 6. Quality Assurance (Q&A)
- **Lab Testing:** Each batch is tested for:
  - Microbial count (CFU/g).
  - Heavy metals (Pb, As, Hg).
  - Ingredient purity.
- **Shelf Life:** 12-18 months in vacuum-sealed packaging.

## 7. Packaging & Logistics
- **Vessel:** Airtight glass or PET jars with aluminum induction seal.
- **Storage:** Cool, dry place avoid direct sunlight.

---

### Manufacturing Planning Table

| Component | Measurement Unit | Target |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Raw Material Moisture | % | 75% - 90% |
| Post-Flash Moisture | % | < 3.5% |
| Particle Size | Microns | 75μm |
| Mixing Uniformity | % | > 98% |
| Packaging Seal | PSI | 15 (Leak Test) |
